'''Kendal Power Station''' is a coal-fired power station in [[Mpumalanga]], [[South Africa]].

==History==
Kendal was built between 1982 and 1993. The first unit went online in 1988.

==Power generation==
Power generation is done by six 686&nbsp;MW units for a total installed capacity of 4,116&nbsp;MW. Turbine [[Maximum Continuous Rating]] is 16.67%

